Fast systems language, powerful, used in games and performance code, complicated and easy to misuse

Common type sizes:

| Type | Size |
| --- | --- |
| bool | usually 1 byte |
| char | 1 byte |
| wchar_t | 2 bytes on Windows, usually 4 bytes on Linux/macOS |
| short | usually 2 bytes |
| int | usually 4 bytes |
| long | 4 bytes on Windows, usually 8 bytes on 64-bit Linux/macOS |
| long long | usually 8 bytes |
| float | usually 4 bytes |
| double | usually 8 bytes |
| long double | varies, often 8, 12, or 16 bytes |
| pointer | 4 bytes on 32-bit systems, 8 bytes on 64-bit systems |

Fixed-width types from <cstdint>, like int8_t, int16_t, int32_t, and int64_t, are exactly 1, 2, 4, and 8 bytes when available.
